    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.98a-98b_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">81-2</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">98a</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        225 Willard Way, Ithaca <hi rend="caps">N.Y.</hi>
                        Jun 3, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear John: - </salute></opener> <p>Your letter, as always, brought us something of the warmth of your personality. It was so good to hear from you, and to know that you arrived safely. But what a risk it was! I should have been broken-hearted had your plane burst into flames. You don't speak of the behavior of the passengers, but I'll bet that you and the pilot were the coolest persons aboard.</p>
                
                <p>I have just finished writing to the persons whom you mentioned, giving each your message of remembrance, that is to all save Thompson, when I <unclear>expect to see</unclear> this afternoon. In each letter I enclosed a copy of Black Elk's "Word-Reader" appraisal, and of his Prayer. So many &#8212; students as well as professors &#8212; have asked about you and have expressed appreciation both of you and of your poetry.</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.98a-98b_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">98b</fw>
                
                <p>Both were, I think, revelations to them.</p>
                
                <p>The alumni have, I believe, in the main, backed Molott. There's still talk, but the whole matter <del>is</del> seems to be winding down. At least it is no longer boiling. The faculty has taken no action. Then student leaders got off easily &#8212; a reprimand on their records. One nice thing happened. Some students in the school of Hotel Admin. baked a cake for prof. Molett, and presented it with the comment that any eggs <del>directed toward</del> <add>intended for</add> him should be used in that manner.</p>
                
                <p>It was wonderful to have had a whole week of you. How much, how very much, you have done for my life, and for the lives of others. Just by being yourself. I have thought of you so much, <unclear>knowing</unclear> that you were going back to a house full of precious memories and redolent of the spirit of Her. Do be careful, particularly about falling, my dear friend,</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Love from</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Slade</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
